Ex. No:  — Importing and Visualizing a Dataset using Matplotlib
Aim

To visualize dataset using Matplotlib basic plots.

Theory

Matplotlib is used for graphical representation of data such as line plot, bar plot, and scatter plot.

Program
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

# Load dataset
data = pd.read_csv('data.csv')

# Line Plot
plt.plot(data.index, data.iloc[:, 0])
plt.title('Line Plot')
plt.show()

# Bar Plot
plt.bar(data.index[:5], data.iloc[:5, 0])
plt.title('Bar Plot')
plt.show()

# Scatter Plot
plt.scatter(data.index, data.iloc[:, 0])
plt.title('Scatter Plot')
plt.show()


Procedure
Open Jupyter Notebook.
Import Pandas and Matplotlib.
Load CSV dataset.
Display dataset using head().
Create line plot using plot().
Add graph title.
Create bar plot using bar().
Create scatter plot using scatter().
